our data is only permitted by our authorized personnel, employees, and associates, solely for the purposes stated above.\r\n<h4>YOUR RIGHTS AS A DATA SUBJECT</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>You have the right to access your personal data. This entails being informed by us about whether and which data we process. You may request information about the purpose of the processing, the types of data we retain, to whom we disclose it, the duration of storage, whether automated decision-making processes are used, as well as other rights such as correction, deletion, restriction of processing, and the right to lodge a complaint with the Data Protection Authority.</li>\r\n 	<li>You have the right to correct inaccurate personal data. If you discover any errors in your personal data, you may request correction.</li>\r\n 	<li>You have the right to erasure (right to be forgotten). You may request the deletion of your data if it is no longer necessary for the aforementioned processing purposes or if you wish to withdraw your consent, provided it is the sole legal basis.</li>\r\n 	<li>You have the right to data portability. You may request to receive the data you have provided in a readable format or ask us to transfer it to another controller.</li>\r\n 	<li>You have the right to restrict processing. You may request the restriction of processing while your objection is being assessed.</li>\r\n 	<li>You have the right to object to the processing of your data. You may object to the processing of your data or withdraw your consent, and we will cease processing your data unless there are overriding legitimate reasons.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>EXERCISING YOUR RIGHTS</h4>\r\nTo exercise your rights, please address your request in writing to the company via email.\r\n\r\nFor any inquiries, suggestions, or statements related to these matters, please contact us via email or by using the contact form provided.\r\n\r\nThrough the aforementioned channels, you may also contact us for updates on the progress of your requests.\r\n<h4>HANDLING OF REQUESTS</h4>\r\nWe will respond to your requests promptly and free of charge, within one (1) month of receiving your request. However, if your request is complex or if there is a high volume of requests, we will inform you within one month if an additional two (2) month extension is required, within which we will respond to you.\r\n\r\nIf your requests are manifestly unfounded or excessive, particularly due to their repetitive nature, we may charge a reasonable fee to cover administrative costs or refuse to respond to the request.\r\n<h4>APPLICABLE LAW</h4>\r\nWe process your Data in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation, as well as with relevant national and European laws and regulations governing the protection of personal data.\r\n<h4>MODIFICATION OF THIS POLICY</h4>\r\nWe will update this Policy as necessary. In the event of significant changes to the Policy or our use of your Personal Information, we will notify you through prominent notices prior to the changes taking effect, or through other appropriate means. We encourage you to review this Policy regularly to stay informed about the protection of your Data.\r\n\r\nThe Company is the Data Processor responsible for processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Updated 11 April 2024.</strong>', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-04-30 09:30:44', '2024-04-30 09:30:44', '', 3, 'http://localhost/gaiaexclusiveretreats.com/?p=377', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(378, 2, '2024-04-30 09:50:27', '2024-04-30 09:50:27', 'By booking your retreat with us, you are agreeing to the following Terms and Conditions - which may be amended from time to time - and all applicable laws and regulations. You hereby certify that you are fully aware that there is a release of liability included, you accept all Terms and Conditions, and you agree of your own free will to all Terms and Conditions and applicable policies below. Your registration to any organized Retreat which is incorporated into one of our organized retreats is equivalent to an annex to the contract of terms of participation legally binding for both parties and acceptance is equivalent to signing them.\r\n\r\nPlease note that these Conditions of Participation contain general information and the rights and obligations of the two parties to the organized retreat, while the specific and particular information (destinations, prices, departure and return dates and times, means of transport, accommodation, visits, etc.) relating to each individual organized retreat should be obtained from the itinerary of each trip and the relevant price list. It is your responsibility to thoroughly review and comprehend our cancellation policy before making a reservation.\r\n\r\nBy agreeing to these terms and conditions, you affirm that:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>You have authorized us to use the Debit/Credit card and/or PayPal account provided.</li>\r\n 	<li>You will not initiate chargebacks, disputes, or reversals of any payments.</li>\r\n 	<li>We retain the right to ban any account or individual without prior notice for any reason.</li>\r\n 	<li>You have thoroughly read and agreed to the Terms &amp; Conditions.</li>\r\n 	<li>You consent to abide by the Terms and Conditions as well as all provisions outlined above and below. No refunds for deposits will be provided.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>About Gaia Exclusive Retreats</h4>\r\nGaia Exclusive Retreats are provided by a sole proprietorship with limited liability under the company name “Gaia Essence LTD” (company no 207660452) established and existing under the laws of Bulgaria. Its principal place of business is Sofia, Bulgaria.\r\n<h4>Passports, Visas and Documents</h4>\r\nIt is the responsibility of each participant to obtain a valid passport, visa(s) and necessary certificates for any country to be visited in connection with a Gaia Exclusive Retreats.\r\nTo participate in Gaia Exclusive Retreats, you must possess a valid passport and have the capability to travel to our destinations independently.\r\n<h4>Travel Insurance</h4>\r\nGuests must have adequate travel insurance to cover the retreat activities.\r\n\r\nPlease note, even if you have private health insurance in Greece or your respective Country of residence, it is unlikely that this insurance will cover overseas trips such as the retreats offered by Gaia Exclusive Retreats.\r\n\r\nIt is your responsibility to organize suitable travel and health insurance. Although we strongly encourage you to do so, you acknowledge that Gaia Exclusive Retreats is not in the business of providing insurance products and cannot be held liable if your failure to arrange suitable insurance coverage leaves you exposed, medically, financially or otherwise.\r\n<h4>Payment Policy</h4>\r\nTo reserve a spot on a Gaia Exclusive Retreats, a non-refundable fee of 800€ is required to secure your booking with us. Due to the exclusivity and limited availability, deposits are non-refundable. No refunds for deposits will be provided under any circumstances at any time, except for cancelation within 24 hours from receiving the confirmation of your booked, as mentioned below.\r\n\r\nThe full payment (due amount) can be paid at once or in two (2) instalments.\r\n\r\nAll retreat payments are due 45 days prior to the start date of the booked retreat unless otherwise specified. Failure to complete all payments by the due date will result in forfeiture of entry to Gaia Exclusive Retreats, with no refunds issued.\r\n\r\nThe retreat prices are charged per person and DO NOT include flights.\r\n<h4>Cancellation Policy</h4>\r\nIf you need to cancel your retreat with Gaia Exclusive Retreats, cancellation fees will be applicable. All cancellations must be submitted in writing. Any promotional inclusions (such as offered products) will be deducted from any applicable refund.\r\n\r\nIf, for any reason, you need to cancel your retreat after booking with us, the following refund policy will apply:\r\n\r\nWithin 24 hours of booking: Once you receive confirmation of your booking, you have an additional 24 hours to cancel and receive a full refund, including the deposit/booking fee.\r\n\r\nAfter this period, the following conditions will apply:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>120 days or more: A full refund minus a 5% administrative charge will be provided for all cancellations made up to 120 days prior to booked retreat start date. This excludes the non-refundable 800€ per person booking fee.</li>\r\n 	<li>Between 120 - 90 days: A 50% refund will be provided for cancellations made between 90-119 days prior to booked retreat start date. This excludes the non-refundable 800€ per person booking fee.</li>\r\n 	<li>Between 60 - 90 days: A 25% refund will be provided for cancellations made between 60-89 days prior to booked retreat start date. This excludes the non-refundable 800€ per person booking fee.</li>\r\n 	<li>Less than 60 days: No refund will be provided for cancellations made between 59-0 days prior to booked retreat start date. Cancellations less than 60 days before the start date are non-refundable and will result in a 100% loss of revenue.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNo refund will be provided for early departure from the retreat or failure to attend the retreat for any reason.\r\n\r\nNo refund will be provided for only part of a booking. For example, if a room is booked for two guests sharing and one guest cannot attend, the entire booking must be cancelled for the above refund policy to apply.\r\n\r\nNo refund will be provided for any room downgrades after the 24-hour period from the time of booking has elapsed.\r\n\r\nIf paying via instalments, the above conditions will apply based on the total price of your booking, not just on any instalments paid. Additionally, due to administration, an additional 5% will be charged on all stage payments.\r\n\r\nAll retreat payments are due 45 days prior to the start date of the booked retreat unless otherwise specified. Clients whose balances are not received by the 45-day deadline risk forfeiting their retreat booking.\r\n\r\nIf The Retreat Has To Close For Any Reason: If the retreat has to close for any reason, we will inform you as soon as possible. Gaia Exclusive Retreats will provide full refunds if this occurs. Gaia Exclusive Retreats will refund the retreat cost if applicable but will not cover any losses incurred with flights.\r\n<h4>Changing weeks</h4>\r\nIt is feasible to change your booking week more than 90 days prior to booked retreat start date. However, this adjustment may result in a 50€ administrative fee per booking, in addition to any variance in the rate of the newly booked room (if applicable). Subject to availability.\r\n<h4>Flights and Transfers</h4>\r\nFlights should be booked independently after confirming your retreat stay with one of our booking managers. If booking online, please wait for confirmation from Gaia Exclusive Retreats team before booking any flights.\r\n\r\nTransfers from the airport to the retreat and back, outside our scheduled transfers included in our packages, are available at an additional cost from our trusted 3rd party specialist Travel Agent, with whom we have been working for years. Please note that if you choose to book transfers through the 3rd party, your flight details will be needed by the week before your departure at the latest. This is to ensure that your transfers can be arranged with our transfer company. Failure to do so may result in extended waiting times for the next available group transfer or the need to organize any-time transfers at an extra cost through the 3rd party. Guests are free to organize their own transportation, such as a taxi, instead of arranging transfers with our 3rd party specialist. However, please be aware that taxi costs may vary for the one-way journey. Clients who arrange transfers independently will be responsible for their transfers. It is worth noting that most of our retreat destinations are situated in remote areas, and individuals arriving on independent transfers often face challenges such as getting lost and being overcharged for the journey.\r\n<h4>Room Damages</h4>\r\nIf you cause any damages in your room or at the property within it, we will deduct the cost of repairing/replacing/redecorating from your registered card automatically.\r\n<h4>Comments and Complaints</h4>\r\nIf you experience any discomfort or dissatisfaction with the retreat for any reason, kindly notify your Retreat Manager promptly, and we will make every effort to address the situation accordingly. Please be advised that any claims may be declined if we are not afforded the opportunity to rectify the issues during your stay.\r\n<h4>Health Restrictions</h4>\r\nIf you are currently pregnant or under medical or psychiatric supervision, you are required to furnish a medical certificate affirming your suitability for travel and participation in the retreat, in addition to notifying Gaia Exclusive Retreats. It is advised that individuals grappling with profound emotional or psychological challenges or seeking therapeutic intervention refrain from attending, as our team lacks professional credentials in these specialized areas.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, our team does not possess medical expertise or comprehensive knowledge of individual medical backgrounds, thereby rendering them unable to dispense tailored medical advice during the retreat.\r\n\r\nFor mild exercise and cold baths, a health certificate is required.\r\n\r\nCertain sections of the retreat premises may be inaccessible to individuals with mobility impairments. If uncertain, it is recommended to seek counsel from a medical professional before engaging in physical activities or undergoing treatments.\r\n\r\nMinors under the age of 18 are prohibited from booking or attending the retreat without adult supervision.\r\n<h4>Force Majeure</h4>\r\nGaia Exclusive Retreats shall not be responsible for not fulfilling its contractual obligations to the extent that the failure to fulfill is due to events outside its control, that is, force majeure events such as a pandemic, flood, cancellation of flights or/and prohibition of sailing due to adverse weather conditions, war, acts of terrorism, riot, civil commotion, governmental actions (excluding regulatory change), labour disputes, and any similar events. In such force majeure events, no refund shall be granted, and all payments will be credited in the form of a voucher valid for one (1) year from the start date of the canceled retreat.\r\n<h4>Reservation of Rights</h4>\r\nGaia Exclusive Retreats reserves the right to make any changes deemed necessary to our retreats.\r\n\r\nWe hold the right to replace the retreat teacher (e.g. yoga teacher) in case of illness, sickness or any other emergency or force majeure reason and there is no refund in this case.\r\n\r\nWe hold the right to change the premises (villa - venue) that the retreat takes place due to any emergency circumstances into an equal quality premise.\r\n<h4>Photo / Video Release Form</h4>\r\nYou hereby grant Gaia Exclusive Retreats the right and permission to use photos and videos in which you are featured and were taken during the retreat. We hold the right to use this material for advertising and promotional purposes. You hereby release and discharge Gaia Exclusive Retreats from any claims and demands arising out of the use of the photographs and footage, without limitation of any and all claims for libel or invasion of privacy.\r\n<h4>Indemnity</h4>\r\nYou hereby agree to fully indemnify without limitation any trainer(s), director(s) or contractor(s) against any injury, malpractice, mishap, or accident during any and all interactions with the Company away from, or at the primary place of business for Gaia exclusive Retreats. Additionally, you pledge to defend, indemnify, and exonerate us, including our subsidiaries, affiliates, and all of our respective officers, agents, partners, and employees, from and against any losses, damages, liabilities, claims, or demands, including reasonable legal fees and expenses, brought forth by any third party due to or arising from: (1) use of the Site; (2) violation of these Terms of Use; (3) breach of your stipulated representations and warranties within these Terms of Use; (4) infringement upon the rights of a third party, including but not limited to intellectual property rights; or (5) any overt harmful act toward any other user of the Site with whom you have connected via the Site. Notwithstanding the aforementioned, we retain the right, at your expense, to assume exclusive defense and control of any matter for which you are obligated to indemnify us, and you agree to cooperate, at your expense, with our defense of such claims. We will use reasonable endeavors to promptly notify you of any such claims, actions, or proceedings which is subject to falling under this indemnification clause upon our awareness of them.\r\n<h4>Limitation Of Liability</h4>\r\nYou acknowledge that during a retreat you participate voluntarily in any and all activities arranged by the retreat hosts, and insofar as legally permissible, forfeit your right to any cause of action against Gaia Exclusive Retreats arising from any loss or damage to person or property that occurs during a retreat.\r\n\r\nYou hereby agree to be responsible for your own welfare and accept any and all risks of delay, unanticipated events, inconveniences, illnesses, injuries, emotional trauma or death.\r\n\r\nYou hereby certify that you are physically fit and have not been advised to not participate, by any means or in any manner, in any activity arranged by Gaia Exclusive Retreats hosted by a qualified medical professional.\r\n\r\nYou hereby certify that there are no health-related reasons or problems which preclude your participation in any and all activities arranged by the retreat hosts.\r\n\r\nYou hereby waive, release and discharge from and against any and all liability from your participation in the trip and in any and all activities arranged by the retreat hosts, including but not limited to, liability arising from the negligence or fault of Gaia Exclusive Retreats and/or its employees and/or its collaborators and/or its subcontractors, for death, disability, personal injury, property damage, property theft, or actions of any kind which may hereafter occur to you including your trip to and from activities arranged by the retreat hosts. You hereby relinquish the right to pursue legal action against Gaia Exclusive Retreats, their agents, contractors, employees, and directors for any of the above may occur during a retreat.\r\n\r\nYou agree that this release shall be legally binding upon you personally and all members of your family.\r\n<h4>Changes to our Terms and Conditions</h4>\r\nWe keep the present Terms and Conditions under regular review, and we reserve the right to amend or update the present Terms and Conditions at any time. The effective date is displayed hereunder. Thus, we advise you to review this page periodically for any changes. To keep you informed of any changes to the present Terms and Conditions, we will notify you by prominently posting the new Terms and Conditions on this page. These changes are effective immediately after they are posted on our website\r\n<h4>Disputes and Applicable Law</h4>\r\nGaia Exclusive Retreats and Guests shall make every effort, so that any difference, dispute or disagreement that may arise during the conclusion, interpretation and execution of the present Terms and Conditions, as well as claims related to them, is resolved out of court, with negotiations in a spirit of good faith within reasonable time after the date of the written expression of the disagreement by any of the parties.\r\n\r\nIf a difference or dispute is not resolved in this way, competent for its judicial resolution shall be the Courts of Sofia, Bulgaria, exclusively, which shall decide on any trials regarding the execution and the Bulgarian law shall apply.\r\n\r\nFor any questions or queries, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:info@gaiaexclusiveretreats.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">info@gaiaexclusiveretreats.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Last updated 12/04/2024</strong>', 'Terms and Conditions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'terms-and-conditions', '', '', '2024-04-30 09:50:27', '2024-04-30 09:50:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/gaiaexclusiveretreats.com/?page_id=378', 0, 'page', '', 0);
